http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Focus-on-education-in-%E2%80%98enabling-make-in-India%E2%80%99/article13981653.ece

A three-day international conference on “Enabling make in India — challenges and opportunities for Engineering education” to begin at the KLE Technological University here from Wednesday will focus on the role of education in realising the goal of Make in India and also discuss what reforms need to be brought about in the education sector.Defence Minister Manohar Parrikar will inaugurate the conference. The former Chairman of All India Council of Technical Education (AICTE) R. Natarajan will deliver the keynote address. Pralhad Joshi, MP, and KLE Society chairman Prabhakar Kore will attend the inaugural session.University Vice-Chancellor Ashok Shettar told presspersons here on Monday that the conference would deliberate mainly on how to prepare and reform the education sector to help equip students to contribute for the success of this initiative. It was necessary to have a strong education system, particularly in the engineering stream.In the plenary sessions, Indian and foreign experts would deliberate on issues related to the creation of transformative educational experience, building entrepreneurial ecosystem on campuses, convergence of technologies and manufacturing.